Two useful kinds of model prediction plots are:
\begin{itemize}
\item \emph{Partial effect plots}: these show the models prediction as one predictor is changed, holding others constant.
\item \emph{Interaction plots}: these show the model's predictions as 2+ predictors are changed.
\end{itemize}

